### 03_Prepare_sentinel1_features

This MATLAB tutorial script demonstrates how preprocessed and pre-synchronized Sentinel-1 SAR-derived features are prepared for LSTM-based water level estimation.

In the associated study, Sentinel-1-derived variables extracted from detected water pixels were used as input features, 
including σ⁰VH, σ⁰VV, incidence angle, and Day of Year (DOY). Ground-based water level observations were used as the target variable.

This script illustrates how the final preprocessed Sentinel-1 feature files are loaded and how key input variables are selected 
to construct a model-ready dataset for subsequent LSTM-based water level estimation.

In addition, this step demonstrates the concept of SHAP-guided feature interpretation. 
In the full study, SHAP analysis was used to evaluate the relative importance of input variables at each monitoring station and to support feature selection together with backward elimination. In this tutorial repository, the full SHAP calculation is not included; instead, a simplified SHAP-based ranking example is provided to show how important variables can be organized before LSTM model training.
